text:
People lets make clear aomething what is done is done... Shotaro and Sungchan are now members of the new boy group RIIZE they are still part of SM sense this new group is the first boy group to debut in 7 years in this Compan... 

Yes is kinda bittersweet to know that this two are not part of NCT anymore and even thought they had debuted 3 or 4 years ago as Kpop idols they literally had to start over again their careers that where already build on NCT... 

Ik that theres many people who actually hates the idea od actualy seeing Shotaro & Sungchan being members of another group who is not NCT and not even a unit of the but they are totaly out of NCT ik people didn't like thebidea sense the first announcement ever given fo SM yo the NCT Fandom and i belive the group itself the members of NCT all didn't take it as a good thing at first but lets put it in this way people...

Look to be honest Shotaro and Sungchan didn't had that much of a schedule while they where on NCT and we are all conscience of that manner all of us (fans) alwasy fought for them so that SM could gave them the spotlight they both deserve as idols sense we barely saw them on mv's and stages... and think that SM did hear us and deside to do this big change for the guys this change is a change to grow their personal and individual careers as idols sense they both already had a standard fandom sense when they became a part of NCT in the first place plus they are incredibly talented and all forms and theirs skill are in another level so obviously SM was never gonna deside to kick them out of NCT and the Company in general so sense SM new they had a group who was up to come for teh first-time in 7 years to debut in the Company andnit was gonna be a boy group what better choice to change them from group to group and stablish them officially in actual Kpop Group where they will have all the opportunities they sadly didn't have on NCT as group with to many members that already had stablished units with stablished members in each one except NCT U that is a unit if NCT that the lineup changes all the time to let shine all the members depending of the style of the song they want to do... Shotaro and Sungchan both debuted on this Unit but even thought they debuted in this unit making them an oficial part of NCT they didn't have a stablish unit or identity Unit like NCT Dream or NCT 127 they where just more of the members of NCT they did shine everytime they had the spotlight but it wasn't that much as they can actually do right now in their new group...

Shotaro and Sungchan now have permanent and oficial schedules as idols full schedules for pure work make good money and shine to the infity and beyonda that literary cuz now they are in a more reduce group that still have many members tho but each one can show their akills and talents as idols also the advantage of this for both is that they already have for career as idols sense 3 or 4 years ago where they got enough experience in the Kpop industry and 100% know how to handle things and how hard, stressful but joyful and happy it can be being an idol they know how much of roller-coaster the idol career can be... and this is perfect cuz they are now mentors for those new members who just debuted with them who never had experience being in actual Kpop career and i even believe that lost of them didn't even pictured for the lifes to actualy be part it but here they are... 

Also a fact and this is a strong one in the new group called RIIZE (i think i mentioned this before) ...  is that Shotaro used to be part of the maknae line of NCT same fro Sungchan but now they are the oldest members of the group specialy Shotaro he is the oldest member of the group and he is also the lead Dancer and Choreographer completely stablished he is the dance master for his members who to be hoenst they are incredible dancers but Shotaro always give a extra mile naturaly idk how he does it tho ğŸ˜…... but yeah and Sungchan is a another great mentor for them and well now they ar ethe okdest two so maybe we will see a more mature "hyung" like Shotaro sense now he has the position of being the oldest brother instead of the youngest.. i think he will know how to the mom or dad of the group instead of the baby like he used to be on NCT ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ so this definitely a whole new era of Shotaro and Sungchan for sure and i'm 100% here for it Shotaro is gonna be Shotaro no matter where the heck his at and same goes for Sungchan...â¤â¤....

Also about the collaborations with NCT hey maybe they did used to be part of the babies of NCT and now they are the oldest of RIIZE  but they will always be part of NCT in their heart and in ours as fandom plus they will see NCT members literally all the time for real cuz they are all still in the same Company and we all know how much Taeyong loves this two like he always had said they are their kids and they will always be... so yeah
